Banana puding crunch is good !

I had to laugh because it felt like a joke. The collard greens were not good. I got 4 pieces of wings ( aka 2 whole wings) with a bunch of fries. The wings were tasteless. The funny part of the meal was the “banana pudding”. It was store bought vanilla pudding with a few slices of bananas on top with cookie crumbs. That was straight up disrespectful. Do better y’all.
Food was good but when you spend $40 there should be napkins and utensils in the bag. Come on guys, lets get right
Finally stopped in a got the Fish n Chips with Mac n Cheese on the side.. and the food was good. The fish was fried perfect with chips/fries.  Definitely going back for some more!
Great food and fast service.  Definitely would visit again.

Thelma’s kitchen food is amazing and they have they best banana crunch pudding ever
The Mac and cheese tastes horrible

My fiance and I found this amazing place on the internet as a must stop place to eat in Alabama. Hands down best food we have had during our adventure wedding road trip!!! Anyone passing through please stop by and have a bite!! This place is a gem! Big shout out to Krystal our server!!! Made us feel right at home! The food and service was more than amazing!! You guys rock!!!! We will surely be back on our next road trip!!!!!

I wanted to love this place I mean fish and soul food sides what could go wrong.  I'll start with the good. My fried catfish was pretty good.  However, that is where it ends.  Grits were like watery and salty.  Did I say salty?  One spoonful was  all  I could eat.  Then the yams.  Square pieces with some unknown seasonings just not good.  Lastly the mac and cheese..absolutely no taste.  If only I'd gotten the food others said was so good I wouldn't be writing this review.

Worst 50$ ever spent chicken hard as hell so is the yams the collard greens are sweet only thing that was o not even k was the banana pudding please do better if you don’t have a passion for cooking with love please just don’t do it

I was excited about trying cause i keep seeing them on door dash, but excitement went away real fast. First the yams where disgusting, second the mac and cheese was nasty, it was dry and had no taste worst i have ever had. Now the one star i did give goes to the chicken it was good. I guess i should have ordered the grits it sounds like it the best think in there.
Their food is terrible you will waste your money.

I had to write this review. This is the first review I have ever written before. So I just had Shrimp, Fries and Grits and when I say that was the best ever that was simply the best Grits I’ve ever tasted besides my own and my families!! For those people who said they tried anything other than what Thelma's specializes in that is your problem. Clearly their specialties are seafood and their Grits. Stick to what you know would be good!!!!
This place is a gamble. Foods amazing but their attention to details the worst part of them. All they need to do is get the orders right and they're golden.

They never get my order right. I swear they just hand off any bag to any deliver driver and hope that’s the right order. I have NEVER received the correct order when I order from here. One time the owner had to personally deliver my meal. The workers are careless and will be the downfall of this business. I tried to support y’all but I’m over it. Dueces.

The fish and shrimp dinners are bomb. Everything he cooks is from scratch with love and you can taste it! I’m usually not a fan of banana pudding but this one is amazing. The wait is awhile so call before you get there.

I stumbled on this place accidentally about a year ago and have been a customer ever since.  There grits are EVERYTHING!!! The shrimp taste good as well. Best fish and grits in the South Bronx bar none.

I had a chicken wing dinner with a dude of double mac.  The wings were pretty good, but not enough for a dinner.  It was 5 pcs of a cut up whole wing, so really that's 2.5 wings. The mac was, not so good, but not totally bad, I've just had better from other places.
Personally the shrimp was great !! So is the fish! We need more businesses like this in the community.

Ordered chicken wings and chips and a chicken dinner with two sides.  The order was NOT correct; no "chips/ff", no baked chicken for the chicken dinner plate and NO ranch dressing. The chicken had NO FLAVOR; who puts sugar in collard greens?  What is up with the sorry excuse of macaroni????  Paid $30 for food I wouldnt serve rats with...all Soul food is not cooked from the SOUL...clearly.

Placed an order on Uber Eats without checking the Google reviews.. it has close to 4 stars on Uber Eats... I must disagree. Food was poorly packed, the chicken looked as if it were fried in old oil. Not so tasty either. Mac and cheese is plain with huge pieces of cracked pepper in it. Collared greens are sweeeet. The shrimp was decent. I would never order there again or recommend. Please save your money!
My Cousin from Louisiana said she don't eat grits once she pass Virginia ate them at Thelmas wanted another order. Food was great
Good food fish shrimp grits need to  put more fish on the plates

BEWARE OF THIS RESTAURANT, they serve RAW FOOD. My fried chicken is bleeding out from the inside; it’s completely RAW. Save your money and order from somewhere else unless you like your chicken pink and raw.
Order catfish dinner. 5 small nugget size pieces. Very little fish in each piece. Very discouraged. Will never order from this place again.
The best shrimp my wife has ever tasted!!!
My order was incorrect. The food was burnt, dry and tasteless. If I was able to give zero stars I would. Do not waste your money.

Ordered from there via UberEats. They did not include both of my sides and banana pudding. If you don’t have something you need to call the customer and let them know. Trashy business and customer service. You guys should close down take some hospitality classes and try reopening because right now yall just not it. The food was horrible too. Don’t waste your money or time.
Order was missing items and the Mac was freezing cold as if we dogs
I ordered Mac n cheese and and collard greens. The Mac n cheese wasn’t seasoned and not so tastey and the collard greens was sweet and soggy.

I ordered the Chicken Dinner w/2 sides for delivery.... it came with one side.  I called the restaurant and they blamed it on the driver, saying the driver removed the side.  He became almost indignant saying he knows for sure he prepared the order right. FOH.... and then to top it off it was NASTY as hell.  Save your MONEY!
My food came back completely raw inside chicken and fish
Excellent Food
They have the best grits I’ve ever tasted!!
The food was good.not what was advertised. They're service was slow. Didn't have any change.  it's not all about the quality of the food but the quantity.
Best fish fry in the entire Bronx!  Whatever you order food is cooked with plenty of love & soul and seasoned to perfection.   Pick up or delivery service is awesome!

The food was disgusting the chicken was completely  raw with blood dripping out of it. My daughter bit into a piece before I noticed. Called and spoke to a male who identified himself as the manager and claimed to have watched chicken be cooked himself and doubted my claim. asked me to send him pictures which I did and of course no apology no response nothing. DO NOT MAKE THE MISTAKE OF ORDERING FROM HERE
The food is banging, They got the best grits in the bx
I love the food. Grits, shrimps, tenders are awesome. This is my 4th order so its time to go in. Garry a pleasure to meet you. Happy holidays Thelma's Kitchen
Just all right
I know a canned green when I taste one . Waste of money and took entirely too long to get here. If you’re seeking genuine soul food, good luck.
Fried Shrimp, Mac And Chesse And Yams!!!
This place is ran by a small amount of people and the food is delicious. Not much room to sit and enjoy but the service is fast and the food is worth it.

I would give them no stars The food is microwaved don’t eat hear they reuse the same oil for fish and chicken , nothing is fresh the server yams diced up with the skin still on it and they have no flavor it’s juss the worse $30 I ever spent on soul food I’m very disappointed Thelma 👎🏾👎🏾👎🏾👎🏾👎🏾👎🏾
Ordered multiple times from here and every time there is something missing from order. The food is fine it's the service that's causing the 2 star. They must do better with organizing the food.

The four star rating is solely based on the grits here which I love. The shrimp and chicken have a nice batter and taste. I wish the portions were bigger but I enjoy the food every time. I know that the sides are reheated but I don’t know if that takes away from the flavor or not. A restaurant that serves homestyle southern food in this area is rare so I want to keep this place in business and will be ordering often.
Very delicious

I went there looking for a fresh soul food meal. No no no.... they tried to take my sides out the cooler microwave and REHEAT it for my meal.... are they crazy! I want fresh made soul food keep your reheated sides. I end up having to get some of my money back and only left with shrimp really a waste of my time! Never going back there again
The food here is SLAMMIN'!  Especially the fried Whiting.  Love it!
The best southern food. Grits that can not be beat. And the prices. I completely Stan for Thelma's!!
They left the skins on the yams... idk where they do that at but it was not appetizing. They give you 4 pieces of wingettes (=2 whole wings) and call it a dinner.
Service is terrible and most of the food is either fried or microwaved
the best
Great fish combos.

The food was banging Fish & shrimp perfectly seasoned Grits out of this world Seasoned fries awesome Home made drinks on point That Banana Pudding Crunch is like crack you going back for some more Need I say any more

NEVER ORDER FROM HERE! This place is a joke and a scam!! I ordered from here through Postmates and the first order the delivery person said they dropped my order off but did NOT! The second one the person still hasn't arrived. Both times the delivery people were BLACK females. When I called the restaurant it was a BLACK man that answered the phone and said to contact Postmates. This was a scam. They take money. I don't think it is even a legitimate restaurant and WILL be reported to the City.
Omg everything was amazing. I ordered through Uber eats and everything was so fresh and ready to eat! Great flavor
Very good place. Very cooked food and professional staff.
FISH WAS SOGGY, MAC TASTE LIKE IT WAS DAYS OLD AND MICROWAVED 🤢 ONLY REASON I GAVE IT 2 STARS CUZ THE COLLARD GREEN WAS A LITTLE OK
Food was good and authentic
Great

This place has so much potential. Food gets made to order except for the sides which get reheated in the microwave which takes away from the quality of the food. The catfish lunch special came with fries and the shrimp lunch special came were the grits. It only comes with 3 shrimp but it shows 4 on the menu. I will give them another try and take pictures next time to share with you all.
Food is amazing their 🍤🍤🍤 & Grits are 👍! !!

I ordered from postmate and I am not one to write a bad review but their food was so bad I feel compelled to complain. I ordered the dark meat large fried chicken dinner I received 3 drumettes and two wing tips. The greens were too salty and sweet the sweet potatoes werent peeled and the mac and cheese was tasteless the chicken was swimming in old grease. I through it out in addition the food was late and my 2 lemonades were missing. Save your money and eat somewhere else anywhere. Another dissatisfied customer

Excellent Seafood. Great Tasting!!!!

This food was absolutely disgusting! I payed over $60 ordering this food. Their portions are very small. I ordered chicken it was burned, and the candied yams were dark brown with the skin still on it, this was by far the worst experience i ever had ordering food and i usually dont write reviews if i dont like some thing but this was horrible!

The food was horrible no flavor or seasoning the portion  was small and food uncooked the mac and cheese was disgusting and when delivered the food presentation was ugly the containers was mashed and partial open. I will never order or visit this place ever again. This was a first and last experience.
Best grits I ever tasted (don't tell my mama). Catfish was delicious mac n cheese was good. Everything was perfect.  Nice owner. Whole family is full and very happy. We will be back....often.
Food was cold and flavorless grits was to thick fish taste and smelt old waste of my money. Period
Delicious Shrimp and catfish
greatest food spot in the boroughs

The food was good. I had the fried fish, Mac and cheese and yams and banana pudding.  Fried fish was fried a little hard for my taste. Mac and cheese was ok. Yams was ok.  Overall I enjoyed the main course.  I would order again.  It is not easy finding soul food in the Bronx. It’s good when you want a little taste of Harlem and you can’t get there.  Now let’s talk about the banana pudding! When I tell you that’s the best banana pudding I had in years!! I mean I scrapped the container to get every drop! It was mouth watering!! I m mad I didn’t order more good!!!  Love peace and Mac and cheese 🧀 🍽 from the Food princess 🍽
Love this  place , the  food is  delicious ,, friendly & family  place to eat
My husband got the fish an grits OMG they give enough grits to feed 2 an I usually add sugar but no need bc they were GREAT without it. Will be going again.

Definitely great on those days when you dont feel like cooking my order was fresh it was difficult but the chicken wings or half-half lemonade/iced tea didnt make the journey home. It was not greasy but perfectly cooked. Worth stopping by.
